# Thread-scheduling test, ported to gomc.
#
# Classic drove `loadrt threads name1=fast period1=100000 name2=slow
# period2=1000000` + threadtest + a userspace halsampler.  gomc declares threads
# with `newthread` and has no userspace comps, so the counter is captured with
# the file-backed `filestream` cmod (../filestream-driver.sh) instead of halsampler.
#
# threadtest.increment runs on the fast thread (10x per slow cycle) and
# filestream.read captures the count right after; threadtest.reset runs on the
# slow thread.  With the 10:1 period ratio the captured count therefore ramps
# 1,2,3,... and drops back to 1 once per slow cycle — checkresult verifies the
# ramp is gap-free and that at least one reset occurred over 3500 samples.
setexact_for_test_suite_only
load filestream sample_cfg=u outfile=out.txt depth=4096 samples=3500
load threadtest <threadtest.0>
newthread fast 100000
newthread slow 1000000
net count threadtest.0.count => filestream.sample.0
addf threadtest.0.increment fast
addf filestream.read fast
addf threadtest.0.reset slow
